The paper discusses the need for explainability in deep learning models for video recognition tasks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the increasing complexity of these models, which suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper notes the scarcity of research in this area, which could also fall under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
